revision.text:
{{Infobox film | name = A Cow at My Table | image = A Cow at My Table (film) cover.jpg | alt = <!-- see WP:ALT --> | caption = | director = [[Jennifer Abbott]] | producer = Flying Eye Productions | writer = | starring = | music = [[Oh Susanna (musician)|Oh Susanna]] | cinematography = | editing = | studio = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|1998|||}}<!-- {{Film date|Year|Month|Day|Location}} --> | runtime = 90 minutes | country = Canada | language = | budget = | gross = }} '''''A Cow at My Table''''' is a 1998 [[documentary film]] examining Western [[Attitude (psychology)|attitudes]] towards farm animals and meat.
It covers the conflict between [[animal rights]] advocates and the [[meat industry]], and their respective attempts to influence consumers. It was directed, shot, and edited by [[Jennifer Abbott]], who spent five years travelling across Canada, the United States, Australia and New Zealand to interview representatives on all sides. The film intercuts these interviews with images of farm animals and industrial farming operations. It explores what is sometimes popularly called [[factory farming]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vegetarian fair offers fresh ideas and meaty moo-vie|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/427912491.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Sep+08%2C+1999&author=&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Vegetarian+fair+offers+fresh+ideas+and+meaty+moo-vie&pqatl=google|newspaper=Toronto Star|date=September 8, 1999}}</ref>
The filming of ''A Cow at My Table'' drew early criticism from the Canadian meat industry, with both the Ontario Chicken Marketing Board and the [[Dairy Farmers of Ontario]] publishing articles warning of Abbott's actions.<ref>{{cite news|last=Strathdee|first=Mike|title=Farm groups shun filmmaker who faces charge of mischief|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/497844321.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jul+27%2C+1996&author=Mike+Strathdee&pub=Waterloo+Region+Record&desc=Farm+groups+shun+filmmaker+who+faces+charge+of+mischief&pqatl=google|newspaper=The Record|date=July 27, 1996}}</ref>
Music for the film was performed by [[Oh Susanna (musician)|Oh Susanna]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Hall|first=Steve|title=A Cow at My Table|url=http://www.animalliberationfront.com/Practical/FactoryFarm/ACowAtMyTable.htm|publisher=animalliberationfront.com|accessdate=May 3, 2012}}</ref>
