The '''British Woodworking Federation'''<ref>[http://Www.bwf.org.uk The British Woodworking Federation]</ref> is the [[trade association]] for the [[woodworking]] and [[joiner]]y [[manufacturing industry]] in the [[United Kingdom|UK]]. It has just around 600 members drawn from manufacturers, distributors and installers of timber doors (including fire doors), windows, conservatories, staircases, all forms of architectural joinery including interior fit out, as well as suppliers to the industry. 

