The '''Green Energy Wind Farm''' is a proposed wind power project in [[Tulcea County]], [[Romania]]. It will have 200 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitatea.net/green-energy-si-a-amanat-proiectul-parcului-eolian-de-200mw-din-tulcea--din-cauza-legislatiei_564692.html|title=Green Energy şi-a amânat proiectul parcului eolian de 200MW din Tulcea, din cauza legislaţiei|date=2009-07-17|publisher=www.realitatea.ne|language=Romanian|accessdate=2009-07-30}}</ref> with a nominal output of around 1 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] which will deliver up to 200 [[Megawatt|MW]] of power, enough to power over 79,200 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$450 million.

